Class CollisionComponent

All Implemented Interfaces:
ActionListener
public class CollisionComponent
extends GameComponent

Author:
Jason Welch If an object has a collision component, it can be collided with. The "collision volume" is calculated by the objects physical attributes such as size, scale, position rotation, etc.. This component will be registered to the collision subsystem and will listen for collision events. If a collision occurs, it'll be notified in which case it can "response" to the collision. Responses can very greatly and so, depending on the object that creates this component, the response method maybe overrode. For example, a rocket may explode and send out a damage event.
